There are four kinds of literal values supported in SQL. They are : Character string, Bit string, Exact numeric, and Approximate numeric.
Character string :
Character strings are written as a sequence of characters enveloped in single quotes. the only quote character is delineate at intervals a personality string by 2 single quotes.

Bit string :
A bit string is written either as a sequence of 0s and 1s enveloped in single quotes and preceded by the letter ‘B’ or as a sequence of positional representation system digits enveloped in single quotes and preceded by the letter X

Exact numeric :
These literals ar written as a signed or unsigned decimal variety probably with mathematical notation

Approximate numeric :
Approximate numeric literals are written as actual numeric literals followed by the letter ‘E’, followed by a signed or unsigned number
